intro: Musineon vaginatum, commonly known as the velvetleaf, is a flowering plant in the family Malvaceae. It is characterized by its broad, heart-shaped leaves that are often covered in fine, silky hairs. The plant produces small, pale yellow flowers that are clustered in dense inflorescences. Musineon vaginatum is native to tropical and subtropical regions of the Americas. It is often found in disturbed habitats such as roadsides and agricultural fields.
